  "response": "An MBA (Master of Business Administration) is a graduate-level academic degree that focuses on business management and leadership skills. Here are key details about the MBA course:\n\n1. Purpose:\n- Develop advanced business management skills\n- Enhance career opportunities\n- Provide comprehensive business knowledge\n\n2. Key Areas of Study:\n- Finance\n- Marketing\n- Human Resources\n- Operations Management\n- Strategy\n- Entrepreneurship\n- Leadership\n\n3. Types of MBA Programs:\n- Full-time MBA\n- Part-time MBA\n- Executive MBA\n- Online MBA\n- Specialized MBA (Healthcare, Technology, etc.)\n\n4. Duration:\n- Typically 1-2 years\n- Can vary based on program type\n\n5. Admission Requirements:\n- Bachelor's degree\n- Work experience\n- GMAT/GRE scores\n- Interview\n- Academic transcripts\n\n6. Career Benefits:\n- Higher salary potential\n- Leadership roles\n- Career advancement\n- Networking opportunities\n- Broader business perspective\n\n7. Skills Developed:\n- Strategic thinking\n- Problem-solving\n- Communication\n- Leadership\n- Decision-making\n- Analytical skills\n\nAn MBA is designed to prepare professionals for higher management and leadership positions across various industries.",
